refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
intgmp_scan1 resourcea intstart
Scans a, starting with bit start, towards more significant bits, until the first set bit is found.

&reftitle.parameters;




   a



     The number to scan.

    &gmp.parameter; 



   start



     The starting bit.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the index of the found bit, as an integer.
 If no set bit is found, -1 is returned.

  &reftitle.examples;



    gmp_scan1 example


<?php
// "1" bit is found at position 3. index starts at 0
$s1 = gmp_init("01000", 2);
echo gmp_scan1($s1, 0) . "\n";

// "1" bit is found at position 9. index starts at 5
$s2 = gmp_init("01000001111", 2);
echo gmp_scan1($s2, 5) . "\n";
?>


    &example.outputs;


3
9
